# User specification folders.
# `User Spec/` is excluded — it's the operator's working space for spec
# revisions, snapshots, and notes that don't belong in the repo.
# `Strategy Repo/` is INCLUDED in the repo because:
#   - The 5 *.strategy_ir.json files are test fixtures referenced by
#     M1.A1, M1.A2, M1.A3, M1.A4, M1.B6, M2.C1, M2.C2, M2.C4, and
#     M2.D2 unit tests. Without them in the working tree, CI's fresh
#     checkout fails verify (this happened on 2026-04-25 run #41).
#   - They are the canonical examples of valid IR shapes; the parser
#     and compiler implementations are validated against them.
# .DS_Store noise inside Strategy Repo/ is excluded by the global
# .DS_Store rule below.
User Spec/

# Temporary / debug files
ship.errors.txt

# Claude working files
.claude/

# FUSE mount artifacts
.fuse_hidden*

# Type checking / linting caches
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
